# py2mcu Dual License

## License Options

py2mcu is available under two license options:

### 1. AGPLv3 License (Free for Open Source)

For open source projects, personal use, and educational purposes, py2mcu is licensed under the **GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPLv3)**.

**Key Points:**
- ✅ Free to use, modify, and distribute
- ✅ Perfect for open source projects
- ✅ Must disclose source code of derivative works
- ✅ Derivative works must be licensed under AGPLv3

Full license text: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.en.html

**This option is ideal for:**
- Personal projects
- Academic research
- Open source software
- Non-commercial applications

---

### 2. Commercial License (For Proprietary Use)

For commercial, proprietary, or closed-source applications, you need a **Commercial License**.

**Benefits:**
- ✅ No obligation to open source your code
- ✅ Use py2mcu in proprietary products
- ✅ Priority support
- ✅ Custom development assistance (optional)

**Pricing:**
- Individual Developer: $199/year
- Small Team (up to 5 developers): $999/year
- Enterprise: $4,999/year (unlimited developers)

**To purchase a commercial license:**
- Email: your-email@example.com
- Website: https://your-website.com/commercial-license

---

## How to Choose

| Use Case | License Type |
|----------|--------------|
| Open source project (code publicly available) | AGPLv3 (Free) |
| Personal/educational use (not distributing) | AGPLv3 (Free) |
| Commercial product (keeping code private) | Commercial License |
| SaaS/Web service (not sharing source code) | Commercial License |

---

## FAQ

**Q: Can I try py2mcu before purchasing a commercial license?**
A: Yes! Use it under AGPLv3 for evaluation. Once you're ready to use it in a commercial product, purchase a commercial license.

**Q: What happens if I don't comply with AGPLv3?**
A: You would be in violation of copyright law. The only way to use py2mcu in a closed-source product is with a commercial license.

**Q: Can I contribute to py2mcu?**
A: Absolutely! We welcome contributions under the Contributor License Agreement (CLA).

